record_data.record_title: Powerex Corp. FERC Rate Schedule No. 5
record_data.record_plain_text:
POWEREX CORP.
RATE SCHEDULE FOR THE SALE, ASSIGNMENT, OR TRANSFER OF TRANSMISSION RIGHTS ON NON-JURISDICTIONAL TRANSMITTING UTILITY SYSTEMS
1. General Purpose: The purpose of this rate schedule is to provide for the sale, assignment, or transfer of transmission rights by Powerex Corp. ("Powerex") on non-jurisdictional transmitting utility systems in which the transmission provider does not play the intermediary role in secondary market transmission transactions as contemplated under the reforms that the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission") adopted in Order No. 890. 2. Duration: This rate schedule shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements. 3. Services To Be Rendered: Powerex may sell, assign, or transfer to a purchaser, pursuant to an agreement negotiated between them, all or a portion of Powerex's rights to the use of the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system that Powerex has reserved for its own use under a service agreement with the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility or under a service agreement it has acquired from another customer. The purchaser must be an eligible customer under the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility's open access transmission tariff or other tariffs pursuant to which the transmission rights to be transferred to the purchaser were originally obtained from the transmission provider. 4. Sale of Transmission Rights: Powerex may sell transmission rights that Powerex has reserved for its own use from the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility. Powerex may sell, assign, or transfer such transmission rights at the price provided below. 5. Terms and Conditions: Except for price, the terms and conditions under which Powerex will sell, assign, or transfer transmission rights on the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system to a purchaser shall be the terms and conditions governing the original grant of such transmission rights by the transmission provider. 6. Compensation: Powerex shall sell, assign, or transfer any transmission rights pursuant to this rate schedule at a price mutually agreed to between Powerex and purchaser. 7. Modifications: Powerex may unilaterally apply to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this rate schedule under section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the regulations promulgated thereunder.
